    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-09-16T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-09-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="101"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d101">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">561.321D1 Advisory Committee/64</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Canada</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Moffat</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 629</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-09-16">September 16,
                            1941</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Secretary of State transmits, for the information of the Legation, a copy of
                    a telegram which is being sent to the American Ambassador to Brazil<note n="19"
                        xml:id="d101fn19">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>.</note> regarding the provision which is being
                    made in the cotton program of the United States for the exportation of cotton to
                    Canada.</p>
                <p>The Legation is requested to communicate to the appropriate Canadian authorities
                    the substance of the first four paragraphs of the telegram.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
